  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The Quality of Recovery 15-questionnaire (QoR-15) is used to assess postoperative quality of&#xD;
      recovery after surgery and anesthesia from the patient's perspective. It evaluates five&#xD;
      dimensions including pain, physical comfort, physical independence, psychological support,&#xD;
      and emotional state. The aim of this study is to validate a German version of the QoR-15&#xD;
      scale (QoR-15Dt) to measure postoperative recovery in German-speaking patients.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
